The Kaduna Sector Commander of the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Hafiz Mohammed has decorated 120 newly promoted officers in the command. Decorating the officers on Thursday, Mohammed told them to regard their promotion as a call for more commitment and hard work towards achieving the mandate of the corps. He urged the promoted officers to increase their zeal in carrying out their duty, adding that the nation needs them to fulfil their responsibilities professionally. “You must, therefore, redouble your efforts, live up to expectations and contribute to achieving the vision and mission of FRSC. “For those that were not lucky to be promoted, be patient as promotion came from God at the appointed time. “You should not relent in carrying out your duties, but continue to give in your best, because with hard work, commitment and dedication, victory will surely come,” the commander said. 20,621 arrested  for seat belt violation in Anambra ― FRSC I supplied AK-47 to bandits in Niger, Katsina, Zamfara,… Two dead in auto crash in Niger 2020: FRSC boss seeks collective action against road… ALSO READ: Daniel backs Operation Amotekun initiative Mohammad said that out of the 120 promoted officers, seven were promoted to the rank of Assistant Corps Commander; two officers to Chief Route Commander; and 35 to Superintendent Route Commander. “Five others were promoted to the rank of Route Commander and another five to Deputy Route Commander. “On the Marshal cadre, two were promoted to the rank of Chief Inspector, another two to Deputy Chief Inspector; four to Assistant Chief Inspector and one to Principal Marshal Inspector among others,” he said. Also speaking, the Zonal Commanding Officer in charge of Kaduna, Kano, Katsina and Jigawa, Assistant Corps Marshal Aliyu Datsama, congratulated the newly promoted officers. Datsama urged the officers of the command to work harder in 2020. STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SID